Maven 2 JDepend Plugin

 This plug-in produces a nicely formatted metrics report based on your project.  
 
*Available Configuration Options
 
*-------------------------+--------------*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 <<Parameter>>            | <<Optional>> | <<Description>>                                                                                     
*-------------------------+----------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 outputDirectory          | Yes      | Directory where the output files will be located. Default to ${project.build.directory}/build.
*-------------------------+----------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 projectDirectory         | Yes      | Directory of your project. Default to ${basedir}.
*-------------------------+----------*---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+ 
 classDirectory           | required | Directory containing the class files. Default to ${project.build.directory}/classes.
*-------------------------+----------*---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+ 




*How to Use

 
  In the pom.xml, insert this segment.

-------------------
<project>
   ...
      <build>
         ...
      </build>

      <reporting>
        <plugins>
          <plugin>
            <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
            <artifactId>jdepend-maven-plugin</artifactId>
          </plugin>
        </plugins>
      </reporting>
   ...
</project>
-------------------

  Generate the metrics by executing the m2 site plugin.

-------------------
  mvn site:site
-------------------

